'''奥卡万戈三角洲'''（Okavango Delta，或譯'''奧卡凡哥'''<ref>{{cite journal|author=甘迺迪·沃爾恩|title=奧卡凡哥：奇蹟之水|journal=國家地理雜誌中文版|date=2004年12月|issn=1608-2601|pages=42-65|language=zh-tw}}</ref>），亦称“奥卡万戈沼泽”，位于[[博茨瓦纳|博茨瓦纳]]北部，面积约{{convert|15000|km2|mi2}}，是世界上最大的内陆[[三角洲|三角洲]]，由[[奥卡万戈河|奥卡万戈河]]注入[[卡拉哈里沙漠|卡拉哈里沙漠]]而形成，大部分水通过[[蒸发|蒸发]]和[[蒸腾作用|蒸腾作用]]而流失。每年大约有{{convert|11|km3|mi3}}的水灌溉三角洲{{convert|15000|km2|mi2}}的土地，剩下的水会流入[[恩加米湖|恩加米湖]]。该地区曾经是[[马卡迪卡迪湖|马卡迪卡迪湖]]的一部分，该湖泊在[[全新世|全新世]]早期几乎全部干涸。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Ross|first=Karen|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/17978845|title=Okavango, jewel of the Kalahari|date=1987|publisher=BBC Books|isbn=0-563-20545-8|location=London|oclc=17978845}}</ref><ref name=ramsar1996>{{cite web |title=Ramsar Information Sheet |url=https://rsis.ramsar.org/RISapp/files/RISrep/BW879RISformer.pdf |date=20 November 1996 |quote=The total drop in altitude between Mohembo and Maun, a distance of440 km, is only 62 metres, giving a gradient of approximately 1:7,000 only |url-status=no |access-date=2022-01-20 |archive-date=2021-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831015705/https://rsis.ramsar.org/RISapp/files/RISrep/BW879RISformer.pdf }}</ref>

== 地理 ==
[[File:ISS-48_Okavango_Delta,_Botswana.jpg|thumb]]拍攝的奧卡萬戈三角洲]]
奥卡万戈三角洲由季节性的泛滥形成，奥卡万戈河季节变化明显，洪峰在6至8月间，每年约有11立方千米的水流入三角洲。由于三角洲地区地势平坦，其海拔高度變化小於2 m，约60%的水资源因植物的蒸腾作用消失。另有36%因蒸发流失，2%渗入地下，2%汇入[[恩加米湖|恩加米湖]]。<ref>{{cite web |author1=C. N. Kurugundla |author2=N. M. Moleele |author3=K.Dikgola |title=Flow Partitioning Within the Okavango Delta –A Pre-requisite for Environmental Flow Assessment for Human Livelihoods and Sustainable Biodiversity Management |url=https://www.water.gov.bw/images/Reports/Okavango_Delta.pdf |publisher=University of Botswana |pages=8–9 |access-date=2022-01-20 |archive-date=2021-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831015657/https://www.water.gov.bw/images/Reports/Okavango_Delta.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Wehberg |first1=Jan |title=Okavango Basin - Physicogeographical setting |journal=Biodiversity and Ecology |date=31 December 2013 |volume=5 |pages=11 |doi=10.7809/b-e.00236|doi-access=free }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gumbricht |first1=T. |title=The topography of the Okavango Delta, Botswana, and its tectonic and sedimentological implications |journal=South African Journal of Geology |date=1 September 2001 |volume=104 |issue=3 |pages=243–264 |doi=10.2113/1040243}}</ref>

三角洲中大約70%的島嶼最初是[[白蟻|白蟻]][[蟻丘|蟻丘]]，然後樹木在土丘上生根，攔截泥沙形成島嶼。酋長島是三角洲最大的島嶼，由一條斷層線形成，長70公里、寬15公里。當水位上漲時，它為大部分常駐野生動物提供了避難所。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Nature explored:Moremi/Okavango Delta in August|url=http://www.nature-explored.com/moremi-okavango-august.htm|last=Dunford|first=Chris|access-date=2022-01-20|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120055602/http://www.nature-explored.com/moremi-okavango-august.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Okavango delta Botswana {{!}} Mokoro and boating safaris|url=https://okavangosafari.co.bw/|website=Okavango Safaris|language=en-US|access-date=2020-05-29|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120055446/https://okavangosafari.co.bw/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

12月至2月是炎熱潮濕的月份，白天溫度高達40 °C，夜晚溫暖，濕度在50%和80%之間變動。從3月到5月，氣溫下降，白天最高溫度為30 °C，夜間溫度溫和至涼爽。6月至8月的冬季乾燥涼爽，日落後溫度會大幅下降，夜晚可能出奇的寒冷，氣溫僅略高於冰點。9月至11月期間進入雨季，10月對遊客來說是最具挑戰性的月份：白天的氣溫通常會超過40 °C，而乾燥只是偶爾會被突然的暴雨打破。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Botswana climate: average weather, temperature, precipitation, best time|url=https://www.climatestotravel.com/climate/botswana|website=www.climatestotravel.com|access-date=2020-05-15|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120055436/https://www.climatestotravel.com/climate/botswana|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=UNEP-WCMC|date=2017-05-22|title=OKAVANGO DELTA|url=https://yichuans.github.io/datasheet/output/site/okavango-delta|access-date=2021-05-17|website=World Heritage Datasheet|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022101844/https://yichuans.github.io/datasheet/output/site/okavango-delta/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==生態==
[[File:Okavango_Delta.jpg|thumb]]
奧卡萬戈三角洲是各種野生動物的永久和季節性棲息地，現在是一個受歡迎的旅遊景點<ref>{{cite journal |last=Galpine |first=N. J. |year=2006 |title=Boma management of black and white rhinoceros at Mombo, Okavango Delta—Some lessons |journal=Ecological Journal |volume=7 |pages=55−61 |url=https://www.rhinoresourcecenter.com/pdf_files/120/1203674763.pdf |access-date=2022-01-20 |archive-date=2021-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210207165941/https://www.rhinoresourcecenter.com/pdf_files/120/1203674763.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。擁有[[獅子|獅子]]、[[獵豹|獵豹]]、[[非洲水牛|非洲水牛]]、[[非洲象|非洲象]]和[[犀牛|犀牛]]，其他物種包括[[長頸鹿|長頸鹿]]、[[角馬|角馬]]、[[斑馬|斑馬]]、[[河馬|河馬]]、[[羚羊|羚羊]]、[[非洲野狗|非洲野狗]]、[[斑點鬣狗|斑點鬣狗]]、[[獰貓|獰貓]]、[[藪貓|藪貓]]、[[土豚|土豚]]、[[土狼|土狼]]、[[野兔|野兔]]、[[蜜獾|蜜獾]]、[[豪豬|豪豬]]、[[疣豬|疣豬]]、[[狒狒|狒狒]]和[[尼羅鱷|尼羅鱷]]<ref>{{cite journal |last1=McCarthy |first1=T. S. |last2=Ellery |first2=W. N. |last3=Bloem |first3=A. |year=1998 |title=Some observations on the geomorphological impact of hippopotamus (''Hippopotamus amphibius'' L.) in the Okavango Delta, Botswana |journal=African Journal of Ecology |volume=36 |issue=1 |pages=44−56 |doi=10.1046/j.1365-2028.1998.89-89089.x }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Klein |first=R. |year=2007 |title=Status report for the cheetah in Botswana |journal=Cat News |volume=Special Issue 1 |pages=13−21 |url=http://www.catsg.org/fileadmin/filesharing/3.Conservation_Center/3.2._Status_Reports/Cheetah/Klein_2007_Cheetah_in_Botswana.pdf |access-date=2022-01-20 |archive-date=2021-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831015402/http://www.catsg.org/fileadmin/filesharing/3.Conservation_Center/3.2._Status_Reports/Cheetah/Klein_2007_Cheetah_in_Botswana.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Wallace |first1=K. M. |last2=Leslie |first2=A. J. |year=2008 |title=Diet of the Nile crocodile (''Crocodylus niloticus'') in the Okavango Delta, Botswana |journal=Journal of Herpetology |volume=42 |issue=2 |pages=361−368 |doi=10.1670/07-1071.1 |s2cid=46987629 }}</ref>。三角洲還棲息著400多種鳥類，包括[[非洲魚鷹|非洲魚鷹]]、[[非洲水雉|非洲水雉]]、[[非洲琵鷺|非洲琵鷺]]、[[地犀鳥|地犀鳥]]和[[鴕鳥|鴕鳥]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-last=Alonso |editor-first=L. E. |editor2-last=Nordin |editor2-first=L.-A. |year=2003 |title=A rapid biological assessment of the aquatic ecosystems of the Okavango Delta, Botswana: High Water Survey |series=RAP Bulletin of Biological Assessment |volume=27 |publisher=Conservation International |location=Washington, DC |isbn=1-881173-70-4 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Mbaiwa |first1=J. E. |last2=Mbaiwa |first2=O. I. |year=2006 |title=The effects of veterinary fences on wildlife populations in Okavango Delta, Botswana |journal=International Journal of Wilderness |volume=12 |issue=3 |pages=17−41 |hdl=10311/28}}</ref>。主要的觀鳥區是季節性三角洲和靠近水的莫雷米禁獵區<ref>{{Cite book|last=Adrian|first=Bailey|title=OKAVANGO; Africa's Wetland Wilderness|publisher=Struik Publishers (Pty) Ltd|year=1998|isbn=1868720411|location=Cape Town, South Africa|pages=66–73}}</ref>。奧卡萬戈三角洲是71種魚類的家園，包括虎魚、羅非魚和各種鯰魚。魚的大小範圍從1.4 m長的非洲尖齒鯰魚到僅有3.2 cm長的鐮刀倒鉤魚<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orc.ub.bw/downloads/FS3_fish.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-02-02 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706162829/http://www.orc.ub.bw/downloads/FS3_fish.pdf |archive-date=6 July 2011 }}</ref>。

奧卡萬戈三角洲是1068種植物的家園，分屬於134科530屬。多年生沼澤中有五個重要的植物群落：深水區的[[紙莎草|紙莎草]]，淺水區的[[芒草|芒草]]，[[蘆葦|蘆葦]]、''Typha capensis''（開普香蒲）和[[多枝扁莎|多枝扁莎]]在兩者之間生長。通常在多年生沼澤中發現的沼澤優勢物種也延伸到季節性淹沒區域。紙莎草、蘆葦在中等深度的緩慢流動的水中生長最好，並且在河道兩側很突出。在被淹沒的草原上方的島嶼和陸地邊緣發現了不同的植物群落。這些物種根據其對水的偏好進行定位，例如''Philenoptera violacea''（蘋果葉棠豆）需要很少的水，在多年生沼澤的最高海拔處發現，並且在乾燥的季節性沼澤島嶼上很常見，限制在多年生沼澤內島嶼的樹木是混合的棕櫚林。三角洲陸地的特點是草原和林地群落，由喬木、灌木和林下草本組成，基本上植被明顯比沼澤乾燥。雨季旱季分明的氣候是三角洲地區植物多樣性異常高的結果。<ref name=":1">{{Cite journal|last=Ramberg|first=Lars|date=2006|title=Species diversity of the Okavango Delta,Botswana|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/226358917|journal=Aquatic Sciences|volume=3|pages=316|via=Researchgate}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Toerien|first=D. K.|date=1976-08-15|title=Geologie van die Tsitsikamakusstrook|journal=Koedoe|volume=19|issue=1|doi=10.4102/koedoe.v19i1.1179|issn=2071-0771|doi-access=free}}</ref>

奥卡万戈三角洲面臨人類活動的威脅。2021年4月的初步勘探揭示了沉積岩中的油藏<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ltd|first=Reconnaissance Energy Africa|title=ReconAfrica's First of Three Wells Confirms a Working Petroleum System in the Kavango Basin, Namibia|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/reconafrica-s-first-of-three-wells-confirms-a-working-petroleum-system-in-the-kavango-basin-namibia-865139500.html|access-date=2021-04-27|website=www.newswire.ca|language=en|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120055430/https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/reconafrica-s-first-of-three-wells-confirms-a-working-petroleum-system-in-the-kavango-basin-namibia-865139500.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，環保主義者擔心該項目將產生負面的生態影響，並且一些主要水體可能受到威脅<ref>{{Cite web|title=A Big Oil Project in Africa Threatens Fragile Okavango Region|url=https://e360.yale.edu/features/a-big-oil-project-in-africa-threatens-the-fragile-okavango-region|access-date=2021-04-27|website=Yale E360|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120055427/https://e360.yale.edu/features/a-big-oil-project-in-africa-threatens-the-fragile-okavango-region|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-03-22|title=Growing concern over Okavango oil exploration as community alleges shutout|url=https://news.mongabay.com/2021/03/growing-concern-over-okavango-oil-exploration-as-community-alleges-shutout/|access-date=2021-06-02|website=Mongabay Environmental News|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120055426/https://news.mongabay.com/2021/03/growing-concern-over-okavango-oil-exploration-as-community-alleges-shutout/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。納米比亞政府已提出在贊比西地區建設水電站的計劃，這將在一定程度上調節奧卡萬戈河的流量，雖然支持者認為影響很小，但環保主義者認為該項目可能會破壞三角洲大部分豐富的動植物生命<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.okavangodelta.com/about/threats/|title=Threats - Okavango Delta|website=www.okavangodelta.com|access-date=4 April 2018|archive-date=22 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222105527/https://www.okavangodelta.com/general-information/threats/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.macauhub.com.mo/en/2016/03/11/chinese-angolan-project-in-angola-harvests-over-1200-tons-of-rice/|title=Chinese-Angolan project in Angola harvests over 1,200 tons of rice|date=11 March 2016|access-date=2022-01-20|archive-date=2016-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104002158/http://www.macauhub.com.mo/en/2016/03/11/chinese-angolan-project-in-angola-harvests-over-1200-tons-of-rice/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。由於全球變暖，預計奧卡萬戈集水區的年降雨量將減少，氣溫將升高<ref>{{cite book |author=ASSAR |year=2019 |title=What global warming of 1.5°C and higher means for Botswana |publisher=Adaptation at Scale in Semi Arid Regions (ASSAR) |url=http://www.assar.uct.ac.za/sites/default/files/image_tool/images/138/1point5degrees/ASSAR_Botswana_global_warming.pdf |access-date=2022-01-20 |archive-date=2021-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831015657/http://www.assar.uct.ac.za/sites/default/files/image_tool/images/138/1point5degrees/ASSAR_Botswana_global_warming.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。全球變暖的影響可能會導致奧卡萬戈三角洲的洪氾區範圍縮小，這將對該地區的水資源供應以及牲畜飼養和農業活動產生重大影響<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Murray-Hudson|first1=M. |last2=Wolski|first2=P. |last3=Ringrose|first3=S. |date=2006 |title=Scenarios of the impact of local and upstream changes in climate and water use on hydro-ecology in the Okavango Delta, Botswana |journal=Journal of Hydrology|series=Water Resources in Regional Development: The Okavango River |volume=331|issue=1|pages=73–84 |doi=10.1016/j.jhydrol.2006.04.041|bibcode=2006JHyd..331...73M }}</ref>。

== 世界遗产 ==
2014年的第38届世界遺産委員会上，奥卡万戈三角洲被列入[[世界遺産|世界遺産]]名录，登录面积2,023,590 [[公顷|ha]]，缓冲区面积2,286,630 ha<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1159 |title=World Heritage List reaches 1000 sites with inscription of Okavango Delta in Botswana |accessdate=2016-03-14 |archive-date=2014-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140625101512/http://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1159 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

